kind: PXELinux
name: PXELinux chain iPXE UNDI
%>
<%#
Chainboots iPXE/gPXE from PXELinux via UNDI. Make sure the OS has iPXE template
associated and file undionly.kpxe was copied in the TFTP directory under
undionly-ipxe.0 name (e.g. from /usr/share/ipxe/undionly.kpxe or iPXE project
web site). Changes need to be made in the DHCP configuration to prevent from
endless loop.

For more info visit:
http://projects.theforeman.org/projects/foreman/wiki/Fetch_boot_files_via_http_instead_of_TFTP
%>
DEFAULT linux
LABEL linux
KERNEL undionly-ipxe.0
IPAPPEND 2
